# Purpose

Keep frontend code consistent across Blade and Vue parts of the project.

# Rules

- Prefer existing Blade components and Vue patterns used in the same package.
- Keep template logic minimal; move non-trivial logic to JS/Vue methods.
- Use descriptive component and variable names.
- Keep Tailwind classes ordered and readable (per PR template expectation).
- Do not introduce a new frontend framework without explicit approval.

# Good Examples

```blade
<x-admin::form.control-group>
    <x-admin::form.control-group.label class="required">
        @lang('admin::app.marketing.promotions.cart-rules.title')
    </x-admin::form.control-group.label>
</x-admin::form.control-group>
```

```vue
const selectedRuleIds = ref<number[]>([]);
const isSubmitting = ref(false);
```

# Bad Examples

```blade
{{-- Complex discount calculation directly in Blade loops --}}
@php $total = 0; foreach ($items as $item) { $total += $item->price * 1.12; } @endphp
```

```javascript
let a = 1;
let b = false;
```

# Checklist

- Is business logic kept out of templates where practical?
- Are names self-explanatory?
- Are Tailwind classes organized?
- Does this follow existing frontend patterns in the target package?
